text: Hauho is a former municipality in Kanta-Häme, Finland. In 2008, the municipality had a population of 3,934. Neighbouring municipalities were Hattula, Hämeenlinna, Lammi, Luopioinen, Pälkäne and Tuulos. It was merged with Hämeenlinna in 2009. It was founded in 1868. == Other websites == * Official website Category:1868 establishments in Finland Category:Former municipalities of Finland
